20 min
Remove pork chops from marinade, scraping off excess.
Heat oil in a large skillet over medium-high heat.
Lightly season pork chops with salt.
Cook until browned and cooked through, about 4 minutes per side.
Let pork chops rest 10 minutes before serving.
Bring marinade to a boil in a small saucepan and cook until reduced to 1/4 cup, about 4 minutes.
Serve pork chopswith reduced marinade and lime halves.
